Executive Profile
Tracy Vincent Maitland  Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President, Advent Claymore Convertible Securities and Income FundAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships57--
Background

		Mr. Tracy Vincent Maitland serves as the President, Chief Executive Officer, Chief Investment Officer and Portfolio Manager at Advent Capital Management, LLC. Mr. Maitland founded Advent Capital Management, LLC in June 2001. He serves as Portfolio Manager of Transamerica Funds - Transamerica Event Driven. He serves as Chief Executive Officer, President and Chairman of Advent Claymore Convertible Securities and Income Fund and served as its Co-Portfolio Manager. He serves ... as Portfolio Manager of Advent/Claymore Enhanced Growth & Income Fund. He serves as Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President of Advent Claymore Convertible Securities & Income Fund II and served as its Co-Portfolio Manager. He serves as President, Chief Executive Officer, Chief Investment Officer, and Portfolio Manager of The Advent Convertible Arbitrage Fund Lp. Prior to Advent, he served as a Director in the convertible securities department in the capital markets division at Merrill Lynch. While at Merrill Lynch for 13 years, Mr. Maitland advised institutions on investing in convertibles, fixed income, and equities. He was instrumental in introducing convertibles as an asset class to major institutional investors and consulting firms worldwide. Mr. Maitland serves a Director of Managed Funds Association. He serves as a Director of The Apollo Theater Foundation, Inc. Mr. Maitland graduated from Columbia University with a B.A. in Economics.Read Full Background




